
# Update linux.conf and linux patches from ROCKNIX

Rocknix documentation: https://rocknix.org/contribute/build, https://rocknix.org/contribute/modify/#building-a-single-package

linux.conf: https://github.com/ROCKNIX/distribution/blob/next/projects/ROCKNIX/devices/RK3566/linux/linux.aarch64.conf

## download linux source and patches from ROCKNIX
```bash
git clone https://github.com/ROCKNIX/distribution.git
cd distribution
export PROJECT=ROCKNIX DEVICE=RK3566 ARCH=aarch64
./scripts/build linux
# after it downloaded and patched the linux source, you can cancel the build
```

## create .patch file
```bash
export LINUX_VERSION=6.x.x
wget https://cdn.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v6.x/linux-${LINUX_VERSION}.tar.xz
tar -xvf linux-${LINUX_VERSION}.tar.xz
cd linux-${LINUX_VERSION}
git init
git add -A
git commit -m "init"

cp -r ~/distribution/build.ROCKNIX-RK3566.aarch64/build/linux-${LINUX_VERSION}/* .
rm -rf dest
find . -type f -name '*.orig' -delete

git add -A
git diff --staged > ~/TiniLinux/board/rgb30/linux/patches/from-rocknix.patch
```
